A_{simple} &= 24,800
\end{align*}
For the compound interest, with a rate of $7\%$ compounded quarterly for $4$ years, we use the formula $A_{compound} = P(1 + \frac{r}{n})^{nt}$, where $n = 4$ (since it compounds quarterly).
